\markdownSetup{htmlOutput=commonmark}
<<<
This test ensures that the `htmlOutput` option correctly propagates through the
plain TeX interface and that, when set to `commonmark`, it produces fine-grained
renderers for each top-level non-terminal element of CommonMark's grammar for
HTML blocks and raw HTML.

<!-- block comment -->

<script>alert('hi')</script>

<div>
hello
</div>

foo <b>bar</b> baz<br/> <!-- bam -->
>>>
BEGIN document
codeSpan: htmlOutput
softLineBreak
codeSpan: commonmark
softLineBreak
interblockSeparator
inputBlockHtmlCommentElement: b3ffb66dd7e08481fe6b45f4a11c8552.verbatim
interblockSeparator
inputBlockHtmlSpecialElement: dba3735d95b8e26c1629e504c873955b.verbatim
interblockSeparator
inputBlockHtmlRegularElement: 5ed18adb8bdfa2141d18971defaa62ac.verbatim
interblockSeparator
inlineHtmlOpenTag: <b>
inlineHtmlCloseTag: </b>
inlineHtmlEmptyTag: <br/>
inlineHtmlComment: bam
END document
